      <p id="Par13">(ii) Two overlapping reads may have more than one significant alignment, particularly when they come from tandem repeats. RegCloser implements an extended Smith &amp; Waterman algorithm [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR13">13</xref>] to find all the significant overlap patterns between two reads, and selects the one most compatible with the readsâ prior genomic positions. In the example shown in Fig.Â <xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig">1</xref>b, the two reads â£ and â¤ actually come from a triple tandem repeat and can be aligned in two ways. RegCloser selects the correct alignment indicated by the solid line, which is closer to the relative position of <inline-formula id="IEq15"><alternatives><tex-math id="M55">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
