      <title>Estimation of the readsâ genomic positions by a two-step robust regression procedure</title>
      <p id="Par21">Although the false overlaps are significantly reduced by imposing constraint on pairwise alignment, a fraction of outliers may still exist, and even a single outlier can break down the ordinary least squares (OLS) estimate [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR14">14</xref>]. Thus, RegCloser adopts a two-step robust regression procedure (Fig.Â <xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig">1</xref>d) to estimate the parameters <inline-formula id="IEq62"><alternatives><tex-math id="M157">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
