    <sec id="Sec4">
      <title>Preprocessing</title>
      <p id="Par10">In the preprocessing stage, RegCloser first maps paired sequencing reads onto the draft genome using BWA [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR12">12</xref>]. Then, the mapped positions of the paired reads on adjacent contigs are used to estimate gap sizes. Next, RegCloser collects reads that are inferred to originate from the gap regions (Fig.Â <xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig">1</xref>a), and estimates their prior positions in the gap by the insert size. Specifically, let <inline-formula id="IEq1"><alternatives><tex-math id="M27">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
